n <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>regedit<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>.","source":"Run **regedit**."},{"content":"To enable sideloading, set the value of this DWORD to 1:","pos":[7581,7637]},{"content":"HKLM\\\\SOFTWARE\\\\Microsoft\\\\Windows\\\\CurrentVersion\\\\AppModelUnlock\\\\AllowAllTrustedApps","pos":[7649,7736]},{"content":"OR -","pos":[7746,7750]},{"content":"To enable developer mode, set the values of this DWORD to 1:","pos":[7756,7816]},{"content":"HKLM\\\\SOFTWARE\\\\Microsoft\\\\Windows\\\\CurrentVersion\\\\AppModelUnlock\\\\AllowDevelopmentWithoutDevLicense","pos":[7828,7929]},{"content":"Use PowerShell to enable your device","pos":[7935,7971]},{"content":"Run PowerShell with administrator privileges.","pos":[7979,8024]},{"content":"To enable sideloading, run this command:","pos":[8029,8069]},{"content":"PS C:\\\\WINDOWS\\\\system32<ph id=\"ph1\">&amp;gt;</ph> reg add \"HKEY\\_LOCAL\\_MACHINE\\\\SOFTWARE\\\\Microsoft\\\\Windows\\\\CurrentVersion\\\\AppModelUnlock\" /t REG\\_DWORD /f /v \"AllowAllTrustedApps\" /d \"1\"","pos":[8081,8251],"source":"PS C:\\\\WINDOWS\\\\system32&gt; reg add \"HKEY\\_LOCAL\\_MACHINE\\\\SOFTWARE\\\\Microsoft\\\\Windows\\\\CurrentVersion\\\\AppModelUnlock\" /t REG\\_DWORD /f /v \"AllowAllTrustedApps\" /d \"1\""},{"content":"OR -","pos":[8261,8265]},{"content":"To enable developer mode, run this command:","pos":[8271,8314]},{"content":"PS C:\\\\WINDOWS\\\\system32<ph id=\"ph1\">&amp;gt;</ph> reg add \"HKEY\\_LOCAL\\_MACHINE\\\\SOFTWARE\\\\Microsoft\\\\Windows\\\\CurrentVersion\\\\AppModelUnlock\" /t REG\\_DWORD /f /v \"AllowDevelopmentWithoutDevLicense\" /d \"1\"","pos":[8326,8510],"source":"PS C:\\\\WINDOWS\\\\system32&gt; reg add \"HKEY\\_LOCAL\\_MACHINE\\\\SOFTWARE\\\\Microsoft\\\\Windows\\\\CurrentVersion\\\\AppModelUnlock\" /t REG\\_DWORD /f /v \"AllowDevelopmentWithoutDevLicense\" /d \"1\""},{"content":"Developer features for mobile devices","pos":[8517,8554]},{"content":"Starting in Windows 10, Version 1511, additional developer features are available for the mobile device family.","pos":[8557,8668]},{"content":"These features are available only when <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Developer mode<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> is enabled on the device.","pos":[8669,8752],"source":" These features are available only when **Developer mode** is enabled on the device."},{"content":"Developer mode options for mobile devices","pos":[8756,8797]},{"content":"Device discovery and pairing","pos":[8836,8864]},{"content":"(Windows 10, Version 1511 or later, mobile device family only)","pos":[8866,8928]},{"content":"To connect to Device Portal, you must enable Device discovery.","pos":[8930,8992]},{"content":"This lets you pair your phone with a PC or other Windows 10 device.","pos":[8993,9060]},{"content":"Both devices must be connected to the same subnet of the network by a wired or wireless connection, or they must be connected by USB.","pos":[9061,9194]},{"content":"The first time you connect to Device Portal, you are asked for a case-sensitive, 6 character security code.","pos":[9196,9303]},{"content":"This ensures that you have access to the phone, and keeps you safe from attackers.","pos":[9304,9386]},{"content":"Press the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Pair<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> button on your phone to generate and display the code, then enter the 6 characters into the text box in the browser.","pos":[9387,9522],"source":" Press the **Pair** button on your phone to generate and display the code, then enter the 6 characters into the text box in the browser."},{"content":"Developer mode device discovery settings","pos":[9526,9566]},{"content":"Device Portal","pos":[9605,9618]},{"content":"(Windows 10, Version 1511 or later, mobile device family only)","pos":[9620,9682]},{"content":"Device Portal lets you view diagnostic info and interact with your phone over HTTP from your browser.","pos":[9684,9785]},{"content":"You can use Device Portal to do the following:","pos":[9786,9832]},{"content":"See a list of processes running on